description.value: Fragment of red-figure pottery kylix made up of two fragments, handle root at the left edge. On the outside, boy leaning against Ionic column, head frontal, holding a reticule, an aryballos and a strigil; to the right, man with hairy chest seated to right on a chair with a fringed cloth on the seat, wearing a himation around the waist, head thrown back, probably playing the lyre and singing. Painted inscription ho pais kalos in field above. On the inside, part of the maeander surrounding the tondo.
